The information below represents the most common issues customers are encountering or recent resolutions to help you trouble shoot your Quest Product.

The following error occurs when opening SQL Navigator, prior to making a connection. This error only occurs when certain users, who all belong to the Admin group, login to the machine:"Access Violation at address 76EEA685 in module 'ntdll.dll'. Write of address 00404A55"

How to troubleshoot connection errors when logging-in to a supported Oracle database using either a 32-bit or 64-bit Oracle Client.Common Oracle Connection errors:ORA-12154: TNS: could not resolve service nameORA-12505 TNS:listener could not resolve SID given in connect descriptorORA-06413: Connection not openedError: 1.0 [Load Interface dlls failed]Initialization error: Could not find Oracle_Home...

The license key cannot be registered after installation of the commercial version of SQL Navigator. The OK button of the authorization window is grayed out after inputting the Site Message, or the Site Message is not even visible to enter

Receive error "error:install of component has failed 1603" when installing SQL Navigator. Since error 1603 is a generic error, I reviewed the installation log ''sqlnav_6.4.0.1930.msi.log' located in'C:\Documents and Settings\All Users\Application Data\Quest Software\Quest Installer\Logs' (XP) or 'C:\ProgramData\Quest Software\Quest Installer\Logs' ...

On the tool bars, there is the one called "Task Bar (Window List)" and it used to show the windows that were open, but now it shows nothing. Resetting did not seem to help. SQL Navigator has been shut down and reopened many times. How can this toolbar be brought back?

"Invalid authorize key" error message displayed when entering a commercial key at the product authorization prompt. The key worked in a previous install of SQL Navigator.

Where can I find my license key file (QSAuthorize12.key)? What is it located?

Any of the following errors can occur when attempting to connect to an Oracle database when installed on a Windows 64-bit OS:"ORA-12154: TNS: could not resolve the connect identifier specified.""ORA-06413: Connection not opened""Can't initialize OCI. Error -1"
